name: Hazrat Khwaja Muinuddin Chishti
description: Hazrat Khwaja Muinuddin Chishti was the founder of the Chishti Order of Sufism. His Urs is one of the most widely celebrated in the Indian subcontinent, attracting devotees from all faiths and regions.

name: Hazrat Nizamuddin Auliya
description: One of the most prominent saints of the Chishti order, Nizamuddin Auliya was known for his spiritual teachings and kindness. His Dargah is a major pilgrimage site in Delhi.

name: Hazrat Amir Khusro
description: A renowned Sufi poet, musician, and spiritual disciple of Hazrat Nizamuddin Auliya. His contributions to Indo-Islamic culture remain unparalleled.

name: Sayedna Hazrat Ali ibn Abi Talib
titleArabic: سیدنا حضرت علی ابن ابی طالب
description: The fourth Caliph of Islam and first Imam in Shia Islam. His shrine in Najaf is one of the holiest sites in Islam.
